@node abs
@section @code{abs}---integer absolute value (magnitude)
@findex abs
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <stdlib.h>
int abs(int @var{i});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
@code{abs} returns
@tex
$|x|$,
@end tex
the absolute value of @var{i} (also called the magnitude
of @var{i}).  That is, if @var{i} is negative, the result is the opposite
of @var{i}, but if @var{i} is nonnegative the result is @var{i}.

The similar function @code{labs} uses and returns @code{long} rather than @code{int} values.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
The result is a nonnegative integer.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{abs} is ANSI.

No supporting OS subroutines are required.

@*
